Nigeria’s 43 cabinet ministers have donated 50 per cent of their March 2020 salaries to support Federal Government’s efforts in tackling the COVID-19 pandemic in the country. This was contained in a statement issued yesterday in Abuja by the Special Assistant to the President, Office of the Minister of Information and Culture, Segun Adeyemi. The Minister of Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Mohammed, according to the  statement, quoted  the Minister of State for Transportation, Senator Gbemisola Saraki, who coordinated the donation, as saying it was a gesture of solidarity and support for the Federal Government’s efforts at tackling the disease. “This global virus outbreak will require nations, continents and smaller communities to pull together to contribute their resources and support one another. This will facilitate an early resolution of the problem,’’ Mohammed further quoted Senator Saraki as saying. According to the statement, the ministers also commended President Muhammadu Buhari for his leadership role in addressing the COVID-19 pandemic in Nigeria. Ministers donate 50% of March salary to COVID-19 efforts - Mohammed Buhari never sought Saraki’s nod for my appointment – Lai Mohammed Before testing positive for COVID-19, Kyari mingled with govs, ministers, others